#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <sys/types.h>
#include <unistd.h>

int main(){
    for (int i=0;i<3;i++)fork();
    sleep(5);
    return 0;
}
................................................


for 3forks 8 processes are created:
├─bash───ex2─┬─ex2─┬─ex2───ex2
│           │     └─ex2
│           ├─ex2───ex2
│

the tree for 5 repetitions will contain 32 processes
